==================================================
DOCUMENTATION SOURCE OF TRUTH
==================================================

The project's architectural source of truth is the /docs folder.

Entry point:

docs/README.md

Before making architectural decisions, Cursor must consult the relevant documents under /docs.

Required reading depending on the task:

• Architecture decisions → docs/PROJECT_ARCHITECTURE.md
• Plugin vs custom code → docs/PLUGIN_FIRST_ARCHITECTURE.md
• Theme structure → docs/THEME_ARCHITECTURE.md
• Commerce surfaces → docs/WOOCOMMERCE_ARCHITECTURE.md
• Request / cart / checkout flows → docs/DATA_FLOW.md
• Installed plugins → docs/PLUGIN_DEPENDENCIES.md
• Integrations / roadmap → docs/FUTURE_INTEGRATIONS.md
• Security-sensitive work → docs/SECURITY.md
• Performance-sensitive work → docs/PERFORMANCE.md
• Deploy / Hostinger → docs/DEPLOYMENT.md
• Status of features → docs/PROJECT_STATUS.md
• Known debt → docs/TECH_DEBT.md

Rules about documentation:

• Treat /docs as authoritative for architecture and ownership.
• Do not invent APIs, routes, or components that docs mark as "Not implemented yet."
• Prefer documenting policy in /docs over expanding unspoken conventions.
• When code and docs disagree on facts, believe the code and update the docs in the same change.
• When proposing custom business logic, follow Plugin First and the Code Review Rule; cite which doc was consulted.
• After meaningful architecture or integration changes, update the matching core doc.

2. Architecture Rules
Never rewrite controllers.
Never duplicate business logic.
Reuse existing components.
Reuse Design System.
Do not modify unrelated files.
Consult /docs (especially PROJECT_ARCHITECTURE, THEME_ARCHITECTURE, PLUGIN_FIRST_ARCHITECTURE) before changing structure or ownership boundaries.

